          "calculation": "$x^2 - 4x + 4 = (x - 2)^2$"
        },
        {
          "step": "Rewrite function",
          "calculation": "$f(x) = \\frac{(x - 2)^2}{x - 2} = x - 2$, $x \\neq 2$"
        },
        {
          "step": "Identify removable discontinuity",
          "explanation": "The factor $(x - 2)$ cancels, leaving a hole at $x = 2$"
        }
      ],
      "final_answer": "Hole at $x = 2$"
